              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Tritons from the resultant were detected",
                "at forward angles using the highly segmented SIlicon",
                "Detector ARray (SIDAR) covering lab angles from 18 deg",
                "to 50 deg. For particle identification, the SIDAR was",
                "arranged into dE-E telescopes with 100 mu-m dE",
                "detectors and 1000 mu-m E detectors. The radial strips",
                "of SIDAR allow detection of the tritons at several",
                "angles simultaneously, with an energy resolution",
                "between 65 and 115 keV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Rutgers University Barrel Array (ORRUBA) was",
                "used for detection of protons from proton unbound",
                "states of 26Si. Array covered laboratory angles",
                "between the edge of SIDAR (50 deg) and 90deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
